======================================================
04_02_team_summary.sql - DESCRIPTION
======================================================

Description:
This SQL script creates a final summary table that
describes the overall performance of each team in the
dataset.

It builds on the detailed analysis from 02 by combining
all important team metrics into a single structured
output.

The goal is to understand:
- how often each team participates in the league
- how frequently they win, draw, or lose
- how their performance differs between home and away
- and how effective they are in scoring and defending

------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Script
------------------------------------------------------

The script is implemented as a single aggregated query.

It first transforms match-level data into team-level
data by combining home and away matches into a unified
structure.

Then, it calculates:
- total seasons and total matches
- wins, draws, and losses
- overall win, loss, and draw rates
- home and away performance rates
- average goals scored and conceded
- average goal difference

------------------------------------------------------
CSV Output Description (team_summary.csv)
------------------------------------------------------

The output of this script is a compact table where each
row represents a team.

It includes:
- participation metrics (seasons, matches)
- performance metrics (wins, draws, losses)
- efficiency metrics (win/loss/draw percentages)
- home vs away behavior
- scoring and defensive performance

This file serves as the main analytical dataset of the
project and is designed for ranking, comparison, and
visualization using Python or other tools.